      </sec>
      <sec id="Sec11">
        <title>Dataset characteristics</title>
        <p>In addition to the FASTQ file containing reads with their alignments, <italic>SimCT</italic> also saves splice and fusion junctions and mutations supported by the sequenced reads in separate files. Fusion junctions are defined as either <italic>non colinear junctions</italic> (junctions on distinct chromosomes, or in reverse order), or <italic>colinear junctions</italic> with a junction length longer than a pre-defined threshold (300kb by default). This means, that colinear fusion junctions are not necessarily produced by the fusions introduced, but can also result from very large splice junctions of unfused genes.</p>
      </sec>
